  "texts": [
    "The nonsensical concepts are highlighted in blue in Table 5.The first two cases were generated by Llama 2 70B.",
    "In these cases, the standard prompt method struggles to fully capture the core contradiction of commonsense in nonsensical statements.",
    "For instance, in the first case, the standard prompt generates a response that is somewhat relevant but fails to address the specific aspect responsible for the commonsense contradiction.",
    "In contrast, the TIP framework, by leveraging the implicit knowledge grounded in nonsensical concepts, generates an explanation that not only identifies the nonsensical issue but also ties it to broader commonsense knowledge, providing a more humanlike response.",
